  <div class="tool-wrapper">
    <h2 class="tool-title">Freezing</h2>
    <p>There are <b>four main phases</b> in the creation of questions :</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>First</b> : Everything can be modified, questions can be created, automatically destroyed, modified, etc.</li>
      <li><b>Second</b> : Questions are frozen, no new questions can be added, but they can still be automatically removed, and answers can be modified</li>
      <li><b>Third</b> : Both questions and their answers are frozen, questions will no longer be deleted, and students must give their points</li>
      <li><b>Fourth</b> : Everything is frozen, and the users database resets, everyting is ready for the matching</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Please make sure everybody understands this scheme, and make sure to notify users before freezing anything</p>

    <div class="freeze-box">
      <h4>Questions</h4>
      <p>Current state : <%= Config::frozen?(:questions) ? "Frozen" : "Modifiable" %></p>
      <!-- button here -->
    </div>
    <div class="freeze-box">
